{\an1}( <i>bell ringing )</i>

00:23.890 --> 00:25.390
{\an1}( <i>whistle blowing )</i>

00:35.030 --> 00:37.800
{\an1}( <i>playing the blues )</i>

00:59.120 --> 01:00.390
{\an1}( <i>horn honking )</i>

01:04.129 --> 01:05.459
{\an1}D-OHH!

01:05.530 --> 01:06.800
{\an1}( <i>screams )</i>

01:21.090 --> 01:22.990
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAnnouncer: <i>LIVE
FROM SPRINGFIELD HARBOR</i>

01:23.060 --> 01:25.060
{\an1}\h <i>WHERE THE SEWAGE
MEETS THE SAND...</i>

01:25.130 --> 01:26.930
{\an1}( <i>coughing and snorting )</i>

01:28.200 --> 01:30.640
{\an1}<i>IT'S...</i>

01:33.740 --> 01:35.940
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hNOW JACQUELINE,
I BELIEVE IT'S YOUR TURN.

01:36.010 --> 01:38.540
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI'LL TAKE
RAINIER WOLFCASTLE TO BLOCK.

01:38.610 --> 01:39.610
{\an1}OH, RAINIER WOLFCASTLE

01:39.680 --> 01:40.980
{\an1}STAR OF <i>McBANE</i>

01:41.050 --> 01:43.920
{\an1}AND THE UPCOMING FILM <i>HELP,
\h\h\h\h\hMY SON IS A NERD.</i>

01:43.980 --> 01:46.750
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMY SON RETURNS
FROM A FANCY EAST COAST COLLEGE

01:46.820 --> 01:50.120
{\an1}\h\hAND I'M HORRIFIED
TO FIND HE'S A NERD.

01:50.190 --> 01:52.290
{\an1}I'M LAUGHING ALREADY.

01:52.360 --> 01:53.730
{\an1}IT'S NOT A COMEDY.

01:53.790 --> 01:54.830
{\an1}OH.

01:54.890 --> 01:56.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hATTENTION.
THIS IS THE COAST GUARD.

01:56.800 --> 01:59.660
{\an1}A 50-FOOT TIDAL WAVE
IS HEADING THIS WAY.

01:59.730 --> 02:02.400
{\an1}ALL GAME SHOWS OFF
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTHE BEACH.

02:02.470 --> 02:03.570
{\an1}( <i>yelling )</i>

02:03.640 --> 02:04.770
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

02:04.840 --> 02:06.670
{\an1}EVERYBODY UP HERE
\h\hTO MY SQUARE.

02:06.740 --> 02:09.210
{\an1}IT'S SAFE AND IT'S SEXY.
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOH, BABY.

02:10.710 --> 02:11.710
{\an1}HURRY, CHARLIE.

02:11.780 --> 02:13.850
{\an1}THERE IS NOT MUCH TIME.

02:13.910 --> 02:15.480
{\an1}I AIN'T GOING NOWHERE.

02:15.550 --> 02:18.450
{\an1}I BEEN IN THIS SQUARE
PURT' NEAR 30 SEASONS

02:18.520 --> 02:20.120
{\an1}AND I AIN'T A-LEAVING NOW.

02:21.390 --> 02:22.850
{\an1}HE'S DEAD NOW.

02:22.920 --> 02:25.220
{\an1}( <i>laughing )</i>

02:29.260 --> 02:30.630
{\an1}DID YOU SEE THAT?

02:30.700 --> 02:31.460
{\an1}YEAH.

02:31.530 --> 02:32.830
{\an1}WHAT'S GABBO?

02:32.900 --> 02:34.830
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hI FIGURE
IT'S SOME GUY'S NAME.

02:34.900 --> 02:36.530
{\an1}SOME GUY NAMED GABBO.

02:36.600 --> 02:38.440
{\an1}<i>HMM.</i>

02:40.810 --> 02:41.740
{\an1}I DON'T THINK
THEY'RE GIVING YOU

02:41.810 --> 02:43.470
{\an1}ENOUGH INFORMATION, DAD.

02:43.540 --> 02:45.110
{\an1}I'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

02:45.180 --> 02:47.880
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hI'M GOING TO USE
ALL THE POWER OF MY BRAIN.

02:49.580 --> 02:51.350
{\an1}( <i>flies buzzing )</i>

02:54.120 --> 02:56.250
{\an1}\hLOOK, SMITHERS.
GARBO IS COMING.

02:56.320 --> 02:57.390
{\an1}AH, YES, SIR.

02:59.560 --> 03:03.460
{\an1}\h\h\hEVERYONE IS SAYING
GABBO THIS AND GABBO THAT

03:03.530 --> 03:07.430
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hBUT NO ONE IS SAYING
WORSHIP THIS AND JERICHO THAT.

03:07.500 --> 03:09.030
{\an1}WHAT'S THIS ABOUT GABBO?

03:11.900 --> 03:13.810
{\an1}I CAN'T BELIEVE IT--

03:13.870 --> 03:15.710
{\an1}OUR FIRST GLIMPSE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOF GABBO.

03:15.770 --> 03:17.040
{\an1}HE'LL TELL US
\hWHAT TO DO.

03:20.450 --> 03:22.450
{\an1}Hello. I'm Gabbo.

03:22.510 --> 03:24.150
{\an1}And I'm Arthur Crandall.

03:24.220 --> 03:25.820
{\an1}\h\hThat's easy
for you to say.

03:25.880 --> 03:27.920
{\an1}You don't have a hand up
\h\h\h\h\h\hyour <i>tochis.</i>

03:27.990 --> 03:29.750
{\an1}<i>Oy! Hey!</i>

03:29.820 --> 03:32.520
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hOh, Gabbo,
you'll say anything.

03:32.590 --> 03:34.930
{\an1}\h\hAnd you can watch us
every afternoon at 4:00.

03:34.990 --> 03:37.860
{\an1}THAT'S THE SAME TIME
AS KRUSTY THE CLOWN.

03:37.930 --> 03:39.800
{\an1}UH-OH. THAT CUTE
LITTLE CHARACTER

03:39.870 --> 03:41.610
{\an1}COULD TAKE AMERICA
\h\h\h\h\hBY STORM.

03:41.670 --> 03:43.770
{\an1}ALL HE NEEDS
\h\hIS A HOOK.

03:43.840 --> 03:46.270
{\an1}I'm a bad wittle boy.

03:46.340 --> 03:47.510
{\an1}<i>AY, CARAMBA!</i>

03:47.570 --> 03:50.170
{\an1}( <i>upbeat music plays )</i>

03:50.240 --> 03:51.810
{\an1}♪ YOU'RE GONNA LIKE ME ♪

03:51.880 --> 03:53.410
{\an1}♪ YOU'RE GONNA LOVE ME ♪

03:53.480 --> 03:56.410
{\an1}♪ 'CAUSE I CAN DO
\hMOST ANYTHING ♪

03:56.480 --> 03:59.580
{\an1}♪ I CAN DO THE HULLY GULLY ♪

03:59.650 --> 04:01.550
{\an1}♪ I CAN IMITATE VIN SCULLY ♪

04:01.620 --> 04:03.620
{\an1}\hLET'S TAKE TIME OUT
FROM THIS TRIPLE PLAY

04:03.690 --> 04:07.430
{\an1}TO TALK ABOUT FARMER DAN'S
\h\h\h\hPURE PORK SAUSAGES.

04:07.490 --> 04:10.460
{\an1}♪ I'LL GIVE OUT SHINY DIMES ♪

04:10.530 --> 04:13.560
{\an1}♪ I'LL TRAVEL BACK IN TIME ♪

04:13.630 --> 04:16.370
{\an1}♪ YOU'RE GONNA LIKE HIM ♪

04:16.440 --> 04:19.779
{\an1}♪ YOU'RE GONNA LOVE HIM ♪

04:19.839 --> 04:23.940
{\an1}♪ HE'S THE GREATEST SHOW
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIN TOWN. ♪

04:28.350 --> 04:30.080
{\an1}GABBO!

04:32.880 --> 04:35.650
{\an1}THAT DUMMY DOESN'T SCARE ME.

04:35.720 --> 04:37.460
{\an1}I'VE HAD PLENTY OF GUYS
\h\h\h\h\hCOME AFTER ME

04:37.520 --> 04:38.820
{\an1}AND I'VE BURIED THEM ALL--

04:38.890 --> 04:41.730
{\an1}HOBOS, SEA CAPTAINS,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hJOEY BISHOP.

04:41.790 --> 04:43.190
{\an1}\h\h\h\hDON'T FORGET
THE SPECIAL OLYMPICS.

04:43.260 --> 04:44.600
{\an1}OH, YEAH.

04:44.660 --> 04:46.970
{\an1}\h\h\h\hI SLAUGHTERED
THE SPECIAL OLYMPICS.

04:47.030 --> 04:48.370
{\an1}( <i>chuckling )</i>

04:48.430 --> 04:49.600
{\an1}\h\h\h <i>ARE THOSE
OUR RATINGS?</i>

04:49.670 --> 04:51.100
{\an1}LET ME SEE.

04:51.170 --> 04:53.040
{\an1}I LOST TO CHANNEL <i>OCHO?</i>

04:53.100 --> 04:54.240
{\an1}WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

04:55.470 --> 04:57.480
{\an1}<i>Dos huevos, por favor.</i>

04:57.540 --> 04:58.580
{\an1}Aye.

04:58.640 --> 05:00.680
{\an1}Oh, <i>que lastima.</i>

05:00.750 --> 05:03.550
{\an1}I GOT TO STEAL THAT BIT.

05:06.950 --> 05:08.350
{\an1}THIS IS BORING.

05:08.420 --> 05:09.650
{\an1}\h\h\h\hI WONDER
WHAT WOULD HAPPEN

05:09.720 --> 05:11.020
{\an1}IF YOU PUT YOUR TRAIN
\h\h\h\h\h\hON THERE.

05:14.890 --> 05:16.760
{\an1}All: COOL.

05:16.830 --> 05:18.560
{\an1}\hNOW LET'S THROW
SOME CRUD ON IT.

05:18.630 --> 05:20.700
{\an1}HEY, IT'S 4:00.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.540
{\an1}So, you want ventriloquism,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hdo you?

05:26.610 --> 05:28.220
{\an1}All right, watch this.

05:28.270 --> 05:29.440
{\an1}Hello, Alphonse.

05:29.510 --> 05:31.240
{\an1}I've got a riddle for you.

05:31.310 --> 05:33.680
{\an1}\h\h\hWhy is a raven
like a writing desk?

05:33.750 --> 05:35.780
{\an1}I don't know.
\hWhy is a...

05:35.850 --> 05:38.120
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

05:38.180 --> 05:40.120
{\an1}Hey, the dummy
can't hurt you.

05:40.190 --> 05:41.530
{\an1}He's not even alive.

05:41.590 --> 05:43.320
{\an1}He's dead.

05:43.390 --> 05:45.490
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

05:48.090 --> 05:50.290
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

05:50.360 --> 05:52.030
{\an1}OH.

05:55.170 --> 05:57.300
{\an1}ALL RIGHT. HERE'S THE DEAL.

05:57.370 --> 06:01.840
{\an1}EVERY TIME YOU WATCH MY SHOW,
\h\h\h\hI WILL SEND YOU $40.

06:01.910 --> 06:03.370
{\an1}\h\h\h\hMan: <i>CHECKS
WILL NOT BE HONORED.</i>

06:03.440 --> 06:06.980
{\an1}I ADMIT I USED THE CITY TREASURY
TO FUND THE MURDER OF MY ENEMIES

06:07.050 --> 06:11.050
{\an1}BUT AS GABBO WOULD SAY,
"I'M A BAD WITTLE BOY."

06:11.120 --> 06:13.080
{\an1}( <i>crowd cheering )</i>

06:16.890 --> 06:18.260
{\an1}WELL, KIDS

06:18.320 --> 06:20.760
{\an1}THIS IS WHERE YOU WOULD
WATCH <i>ITCHY & SCRATCHY</i>

06:20.830 --> 06:23.360
{\an1}EXCEPT THEY'RE ON <i>THE
\h\h\hGABBO SHOW NOW.</i>

06:23.430 --> 06:26.960
{\an1}\hSO HERE'S EASTERN EUROPE'S
FAVORITE CAT-AND-MOUSE TEAM--

06:27.030 --> 06:29.270
{\an1}<i>WORKER AND PARASITE.</i>

06:29.330 --> 06:30.470
{\an1}( <i>chuckling )</i>

06:32.900 --> 06:34.840
{\an1}( <i>speaking European Language )</i>

06:49.650 --> 06:51.460
{\an1}WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

07:00.430 --> 07:02.200
{\an1}WELL, THAT'S IT.

07:02.270 --> 07:03.840
{\an1}WE'VE BEEN CANCELED.

07:03.900 --> 07:06.570
{\an1}I THINK WE CAN BE PROUD
THAT WE NEVER DID A BAD SHOW.

07:06.640 --> 07:07.740
{\an1}EXCEPT FOR THAT WEEK

07:07.810 --> 07:09.910
{\an1}RAY JAY JOHNSON
WAS MY CO-HOST.

07:09.980 --> 07:11.490
{\an1}♪ YOU CAN CALL ME RAY ♪

07:11.540 --> 07:13.480
{\an1}♪ AND YOU CAN CALL ME JAY... ♪

07:13.550 --> 07:17.490
{\an1}OOH! THAT THING WAS FUNNY
FOR ABOUT THREE SECONDS.

07:17.550 --> 07:20.490
{\an1}BUT THE IMPORTANT THING IS
\h\h\hWE'RE LIKE A FAMILY.

07:20.550 --> 07:21.620
{\an1}KRUSTY, I...

07:21.690 --> 07:22.720
{\an1}SHUT YOUR HOLE!

07:25.420 --> 07:28.560
{\an1}( <i>doorbell playing "Theme
\hfrom the Tonight Show" <i>)</i></i>

07:28.630 --> 07:30.560
{\an1}KRUSTY, HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

07:30.630 --> 07:32.930
{\an1}I'M KIND OF WORRIED
\h\hABOUT THE FUTURE.

07:33.000 --> 07:34.370
{\an1}HOW DO YOU DEAL
\h\h\hWITH IT?

07:34.430 --> 07:36.430
{\an1}WELL, YOU'VE BEEN ON TV
LONGER THAN I HAVE.

07:36.500 --> 07:38.270
{\an1}I'M SURE YOU'VE SAVED UP
QUITE A NEST EGG.

07:38.340 --> 07:40.000
{\an1}UH, YEAH.

07:40.070 --> 07:41.740
{\an1}DO THEY STILL BUY
\h\h\hHUMAN HAIR

07:41.810 --> 07:43.440
{\an1}DOWN AT THE WIG SHOP?

07:45.510 --> 07:47.280
{\an1}( <i>grunts )</i>

07:47.350 --> 07:48.750
{\an1}KRUSTY, YOU WANT
TO STAY FOR DINNER?

07:48.810 --> 07:49.750
{\an1}NAH, SORRY.

07:49.810 --> 07:51.220
{\an1}OH, THAT'S TOO BAD,

07:51.280 --> 07:53.650
{\an1}'CAUSE TONIGHT MY GUESTS
WILL BE DR. CARL SAGAN

07:53.720 --> 07:55.790
{\an1}AND FROM THE SAN DIEGO ZOO,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hJOAN EMBREE.

07:55.850 --> 07:56.950
{\an1}( <i>drum roll )</i>

07:58.690 --> 07:59.720
{\an1}OH, KYLE

07:59.790 --> 08:00.890
{\an1}I JUST DON'T THINK

08:00.960 --> 08:02.790
{\an1}\h\hI FIT IN HERE
AT MELROSE PLACE.

08:02.860 --> 08:06.300
{\an1}FROM NOW ON, I'LL BE DOING
THE THINKING FOR BOTH OF US.

08:08.400 --> 08:09.770
{\an1}( <i>horn blows )
\h\hMan: NEXT!</i>

08:09.830 --> 08:13.640
{\an1}( <i>"Call to the Post" playing)</i>

08:13.710 --> 08:15.350
{\an1}COME ON, YOU STUPID HORSE!

08:15.410 --> 08:17.880
{\an1}I GOT MY LAST TEN BUCKS ON YOU.

08:17.940 --> 08:20.310
{\an1}NO, DON'T LOOK AT ME.

08:20.380 --> 08:21.550
{\an1}RUN!

08:21.610 --> 08:24.050
{\an1}NO, DON'T COME OVER HERE.

08:24.120 --> 08:26.280
{\an1}OH, BOY.

08:29.250 --> 08:31.260
{\an1}\h\h\hAnd now it's time
for another patented

08:31.320 --> 08:33.360
{\an1}Gabbo crank call.

08:33.429 --> 08:34.440
{\an1}Oh, I love these.

08:34.490 --> 08:35.789
{\an1}I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

08:35.860 --> 08:37.830
{\an1}HE STOLE THIS BIT
\h\hFROM KRUSTY.

08:37.900 --> 08:40.159
{\an1}YEAH, WELL, KRUSTY STOLE IT
FROM STEVE ALLEN.

08:40.230 --> 08:42.700
{\an1}\h\h\h\hEVERYTHING'S
STOLEN NOWADAYS.

08:42.770 --> 08:44.370
{\an1}WHY, THE FAX MACHINE
\h\h\h\h\hIS NOTHING

08:44.440 --> 08:47.070
{\an1}\h\h\hBUT A WAFFLE IRON
WITH A PHONE ATTACHED.

08:47.140 --> 08:48.710
{\an1}It's ringing.

08:48.770 --> 08:49.470
{\an1}Hello.

08:49.540 --> 08:50.910
{\an1}Is this Krusty the Clown?

08:50.980 --> 08:53.010
{\an1}Krusty: Is this the callback
\h\h\h\hfor that porno film?

08:53.080 --> 08:56.680
{\an1}Look, I was a little nervous
\hthat day, but I'm all man.

08:56.750 --> 08:57.750
{\an1}I can assure you.

08:57.820 --> 08:59.720
{\an1}No, I represent

08:59.780 --> 09:01.450
{\an1}a Japanese camera company.

09:01.520 --> 09:03.960
{\an1}We'd like to pay you
\htwo million dollars

09:04.020 --> 09:05.160
{\an1}to do a camera commercial.

09:05.220 --> 09:08.130
{\an1}Whoa! Me rikie vely much.

09:08.190 --> 09:10.390
{\an1}I hope I didn't offend you.

09:10.460 --> 09:11.860
{\an1}I need this bad.

09:11.930 --> 09:14.670
{\an1}\hBad enough to hit yourself
over the head with the phone?

09:14.730 --> 09:18.340
{\an1}\hOh, you got it.
( <i>Krusty yells )</i>

09:18.400 --> 09:19.400
{\an1}Ooh, blood.

09:19.470 --> 09:21.410
{\an1}( <i>laughter )</i>

09:22.640 --> 09:24.180
{\an1}What the..?

09:24.240 --> 09:26.210
{\an1}If this is anyone
\hbut Steve Allen

09:26.280 --> 09:28.150
{\an1}you're stealing my bit.

09:28.210 --> 09:29.710
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSOMEBODY OUGHT
TO RUIN GABBO'S CAREER

09:29.780 --> 09:31.480
{\an1}THE WAY HE RUINED KRUSTY'S.

09:31.550 --> 09:32.980
{\an1}TWO WRONGS DON'T MAKE
\h\h\hA RIGHT, BART.

09:33.050 --> 09:34.120
{\an1}YES, THEY DO.

09:34.190 --> 09:34.950
{\an1}NO, THEY DON'T.

09:35.990 --> 09:36.750
{\an1}DAD!

09:36.820 --> 09:39.420
{\an1}TWO WRONGS MAKE A RIGHT, LISA.

09:39.490 --> 09:41.330
{\an1}AH, REX MORGAN, M.D.

09:41.390 --> 09:44.230
{\an1}YOU HAVE THE PRESCRIPTION
\h\hFOR THE DAILY BLUES.

09:46.200 --> 09:47.670
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWE'LL BE BACK
AFTER THIS COMMERCIAL

09:47.730 --> 09:49.230
{\an1}FOR GABBO AIRLINES.

09:49.300 --> 09:51.240
{\an1}AND... CUT.

09:51.300 --> 09:53.240
{\an1}THAT OUGHT TO HOLD
THE LITTLE S.O.B.s.

09:53.300 --> 09:54.670
{\an1}GABBO, QUIET.

09:54.740 --> 09:57.010
{\an1}I WOULDN'T WANT TO OFFEND
\h\h\hTHE LITTLE S.O.B.s.

09:57.080 --> 09:58.390
{\an1}I WISH YOU'D STOP
SAYING THAT.

09:59.540 --> 10:00.340
{\an1}HMM.

10:00.410 --> 10:02.250
{\an1}( <i>chuckling )</i>

10:02.310 --> 10:03.380
{\an1}HEY, BOY-O.

10:03.450 --> 10:04.280
{\an1}WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

10:04.350 --> 10:05.480
{\an1}WELL, IT'S...

10:05.550 --> 10:06.680
{\an1}YOU WOULDN'T BE INTERESTED.

10:06.750 --> 10:07.520
{\an1}IT'S TOO LOW-BROW.

10:07.590 --> 10:09.090
{\an1}NO, I'M QUITE LOW-BROW.

10:09.150 --> 10:11.220
{\an1}WELL, SOMEBODY JUST WROTE
\h\h\h\hA BAWDY LIMERICK

10:11.290 --> 10:12.560
{\an1}ON THE MEN'S ROOM WALL.

10:12.620 --> 10:13.960
{\an1}THIS I GOT TO SEE!

10:17.300 --> 10:19.160
{\an1}ALL THE KIDS IN SPRINGFIELD
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hARE S.O.B.s.

10:20.330 --> 10:21.330
{\an1}GABBO'S KIND OF LANGUAGE

10:21.400 --> 10:23.730
{\an1}HAS NO PLACE ON OR OFF TV

10:23.800 --> 10:26.140
{\an1}AND THAT'S MY TWO CENTS.

10:28.170 --> 10:30.810
{\an1}THAT OUGHT TO HOLD
\h\hTHOSE S.O.B.s.

10:30.880 --> 10:31.610
{\an1}WHAT THE..?

10:35.210 --> 10:35.980
{\an1}( <i>gasps )</i>

10:36.050 --> 10:37.550
{\an1}OH, NO.

10:39.980 --> 10:41.750
{\an1}\hKRUSTY, ARE YOU
MAKING ANY MONEY?

10:41.820 --> 10:44.620
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hNAH. THAT GUY'S
GIVING IT AWAY FOR FREE.

10:44.690 --> 10:47.830
{\an1}♪ THE OLD GRAY MARE SHE AIN'T
\h\hWHAT SHE USED TO BE ♪

10:47.890 --> 10:49.360
{\an1}♪ AIN'T WHAT SHE USED TO BE ♪

10:49.430 --> 10:50.700
{\an1}♪ AIN'T WHAT SHE USED TO BE... ♪

10:53.300 --> 10:55.430
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h( <i>groans )
35 YEARS IN SHOW BUSINESS</i>

10:55.500 --> 10:58.900
{\an1}\h\h\h\hAND ALREADY NO ONE
REMEMBERS ME, JUST LIKE...

10:58.970 --> 11:01.510
{\an1}WHAT'S HIS NAME AND WHOOZITS

11:01.570 --> 11:04.710
{\an1}AND, YOU KNOW, THAT GUY...
ALWAYS WORE A SHIRT.

11:04.780 --> 11:06.440
{\an1}ED SULLIVAN?
YEAH.

11:06.510 --> 11:07.750
{\an1}I DIDN'T KNOW

11:07.810 --> 11:09.180
{\an1}YOU KNEW LUKE PERRY.

11:09.250 --> 11:12.650
{\an1}KNOW HIM? HE'S MY WORTHLESS
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHALF-BROTHER.

11:12.720 --> 11:14.590
{\an1}HE'S A BIG TV STAR.

11:14.650 --> 11:16.790
{\an1}YEAH, ON FOX.

11:18.090 --> 11:20.190
{\an1}ELIZABETH TAYLOR.

11:20.260 --> 11:21.860
{\an1}BETTE MIDLER.

11:21.930 --> 11:23.660
{\an1}\h\h\hBETTE AND I OWNED
A RACEHORSE TOGETHER--

11:23.730 --> 11:25.130
{\an1}KRUDLER.

11:25.200 --> 11:27.630
{\an1}HEY, BART, IF WE GET
ALL THESE BIG STARS

11:27.700 --> 11:29.230
{\an1}TO APPEAR ON A SPECIAL
\h\h\h\h\h\hWITH KRUSTY

11:29.300 --> 11:30.870
{\an1}IT MIGHT GET HIS CAREER
\h\h\h\h\hGOING AGAIN.

11:36.410 --> 11:37.610
{\an1}HERE'S MY ADDRESS BOOK.

11:37.680 --> 11:39.140
{\an1}GO GET THOSE STARS.

11:40.510 --> 11:42.080
{\an1}IT WON'T BE EASY

11:42.150 --> 11:45.120
{\an1}BUT I'M GOING TO CLAW
MY WAY BACK ONTO TV.

11:47.020 --> 11:50.050
{\an1}\h\h♪ The old gray mare she
ain't what she used to be ♪

11:50.120 --> 11:51.390
{\an1}♪ Ain't what she used to be ♪

11:51.460 --> 11:52.960
{\an1}♪ Ain't what she used to be... ♪

11:53.020 --> 11:56.760
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAnnouncer: <i>And now,
the Crazy Old Man Singers.</i>

11:56.830 --> 11:59.500
{\an1}\h\h\hOld mel: ♪ The old gray mare
she ain't what she used to be ♪

11:59.560 --> 12:01.000
{\an1}♪ Ain't what she used to be... ♪

12:06.040 --> 12:07.470
{\an1}MISS MIDLER,
I CAN'T BELIEVE

12:07.540 --> 12:09.270
{\an1}YOU DO THIS
ALL BY YOURSELF.

12:09.340 --> 12:11.340
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hWE'RE AMERICANS.
WE DESERVE CLEAN HIGHWAYS.

12:14.210 --> 12:15.380
{\an1}YOU PIGS!

12:17.850 --> 12:19.180
{\an1}OH, NO.

12:19.250 --> 12:20.620
{\an1}BETTE MIDLER.

12:20.690 --> 12:22.830
{\an1}( <i>grunts )</i>

12:22.890 --> 12:24.490
{\an1}( <i>tires screeching )</i>

12:24.560 --> 12:26.060
{\an1}( <i>loud crash )</i>

12:28.130 --> 12:29.060
{\an1}NOW WHERE WERE WE?

12:29.130 --> 12:30.230
{\an1}WE WERE ASKING YOU
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTO APPEAR

12:30.300 --> 12:31.770
{\an1}ON KRUSTY'S COMEBACK SPECIAL.

12:33.030 --> 12:34.930
{\an1}\hOKAY. TELL KRUSTY
HE CAN COUNT ME IN.

12:39.570 --> 12:42.210
{\an1}IT'S TIME TO TAKE OUT THE TRASH.

12:45.240 --> 12:47.410
{\an1}I'LL GET YOU FOR THIS, MIDLER!

12:51.150 --> 12:52.420
{\an1}Man: <i>AND OFF TO YOUR LEFT</i>

12:52.480 --> 12:54.590
{\an1}<i>IS HUGH HEFNER'S
SHELBYVILLE PAD.</i>

12:54.650 --> 12:56.320
{\an1}A LOT OF PEOPLE KNOW
\h\h\h\hABOUT THE GROTTO

12:56.390 --> 12:57.290
{\an1}AND THE GAME ROOM.

12:57.360 --> 12:58.930
{\an1}OF COURSE.

12:58.990 --> 13:01.390
{\an1}BUT FEW KNOW
ABOUT THE LABORATORY--
THE BIOSPHERE.

13:01.460 --> 13:03.460
{\an1}THE ALTERNATIVE ENERGY
\h\h\hRESEARCH CENTER.

13:07.130 --> 13:08.330
{\an1}FASCINATING.

13:13.370 --> 13:14.910
{\an1}DESALINIZATION PLANT?

13:14.970 --> 13:17.140
{\an1}YES. THE GROTTO USES
\h\h\h\h\h\hSO MUCH WATER.

13:17.210 --> 13:19.010
{\an1}\h\h\hTHE BUNNIES FELT
WE SHOULD GO THIS WAY.

13:19.080 --> 13:20.440
{\an1}SMART BUNNIES, HEF.

13:20.510 --> 13:21.910
{\an1}I CAN CALL YOU HEF,
\h\h\h\h\hCAN'T I?

13:21.980 --> 13:22.550
{\an1}NO.

13:25.620 --> 13:28.250
{\an1}YOU TOLD OUR AGENT THIS PLACE
\h\h\h\hHOLDS 30,000 PEOPLE.

13:28.320 --> 13:30.650
{\an1}IT DOES. WE HAD 30,000 HERE
\h\h\h\h\h\hLAST NIGHT.

13:30.720 --> 13:32.690
{\an1}NOW PLAY-- THE AUDIENCE
IS GETTING RESTLESS.

13:32.760 --> 13:34.730
{\an1}WE WANT CHILI WILLY.

13:34.790 --> 13:36.430
{\an1}WE WANT CHILI WILLY.

13:38.300 --> 13:39.660
{\an1}HEY, RED HOT CHILI
\h\h\h\h\h\hPEPPERS

13:39.730 --> 13:40.870
{\an1}WOULD YOU GUYS
LIKE TO APPEAR

13:40.930 --> 13:42.530
{\an1}\h\h\h\hON A KRUSTY
THE CLOWN SPECIAL?

13:42.600 --> 13:44.440
{\an1}SURE, IF YOU CAN GET US
\h\h\hOUT OF THIS GIG.

13:44.500 --> 13:46.770
{\an1}NO PROBLEMO.
HEY MOE, LOOK OVER THERE!

13:46.840 --> 13:48.370
{\an1}WHAT? WHAT AM I LOOKING AT?

13:48.440 --> 13:50.170
{\an1}I DON'T SEE NOTHING.

13:50.240 --> 13:52.540
{\an1}I'M GOING TO STOP LOOKING SOON.

13:52.610 --> 13:54.210
{\an1}WHAT?
WHAT, IS THAT IT?

13:54.280 --> 13:55.750
{\an1}\h\h\hHEY, MOE,
CAN I LOOK TOO?

13:55.810 --> 13:57.550
{\an1}SURE, BUT IT WILL COST YOU.

13:57.620 --> 13:58.820
{\an1}MY WALLET'S IN THE CAR.

14:00.150 --> 14:01.650
{\an1}HE IS SO STUPID.

14:01.720 --> 14:02.950
{\an1}AND NOW BACK TO THE WALL.

14:07.730 --> 14:10.560
{\an1}( <i>humming )</i>

14:10.630 --> 14:11.760
{\an1}MISS TAYLOR,
A COUPLE OF GRADE SCHOOL KIDS

14:11.830 --> 14:13.530
{\an1}\h\hWANTED YOU TO BE
ON A KRUSTY SPECIAL.

14:13.600 --> 14:15.330
{\an1}I TOLD THEM TO BUZZ OFF.

14:15.400 --> 14:16.500
{\an1}GOOD.

14:16.570 --> 14:19.000
{\an1}( <i>humming )</i>

14:19.070 --> 14:20.300
{\an1}( <i>banging door )</i>

14:20.370 --> 14:22.210
{\an1}KRUSTY, WE'VE GOT
GREAT NEWS.

14:22.270 --> 14:23.340
{\an1}Both: AHHH!

14:24.980 --> 14:27.010
{\an1}( <i>groaning )</i>

14:27.080 --> 14:29.810
{\an1}KRUSTY, WHAT HAVE YOU
\h\hDONE TO YOURSELF?

14:29.880 --> 14:31.350
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hI THOUGHT
I'D GET INTO SHAPE

14:31.420 --> 14:33.550
{\an1}\h\hSO I'VE BEEN DRINKING
NOTHING BUT MILK SHAKES.

14:33.620 --> 14:35.350
{\an1}\hYOU MEAN THOSE
DIET MILKSHAKES?

14:35.420 --> 14:36.150
{\an1}UH-OH.

14:36.220 --> 14:37.690
{\an1}NOW YOU CAN STAY WITH US

14:37.760 --> 14:39.060
{\an1}UNTIL YOU LOSE
\hTHAT WEIGHT.

14:39.120 --> 14:40.220
{\an1}YOU CAN SLEEP
ON THE SOFA.

14:40.290 --> 14:41.560
{\an1}IT FOLDS RIGHT OUT.

14:41.630 --> 14:43.690
{\an1}( <i>groaning )</i>

14:43.760 --> 14:46.430
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

14:46.500 --> 14:47.970
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOH, WAIT.
THAT WAS THE OLD SOFA.

14:49.630 --> 14:51.470
{\an1}( <i>cat screeching )</i>

14:57.140 --> 14:58.710
{\an1}I'LL NEVER GET
\hMY AIM BACK.

14:58.780 --> 14:59.980
{\an1}YOU GOT TO KEEP
WORKING ON IT.

15:01.950 --> 15:02.880
{\an1}AHH!

15:02.950 --> 15:04.980
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

15:05.050 --> 15:07.220
{\an1}MMM... DELICIOUS.

15:10.560 --> 15:11.930
{\an1}OH, WHY AM I BOTHERING?

15:11.990 --> 15:12.890
{\an1}IT'S HOPELESS.

15:12.960 --> 15:13.920
{\an1}Hi, kids.

15:13.990 --> 15:14.990
{\an1}It's me.

15:15.060 --> 15:16.260
{\an1}Gabbo.

15:16.330 --> 15:17.930
{\an1}( <i>laughing )</i>

15:19.630 --> 15:20.760
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

15:22.770 --> 15:24.700
{\an1}\hPork prices rose in
early trading today.

15:26.170 --> 15:27.070
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

15:34.580 --> 15:35.680
{\an1}\h\h\h\hKrusty:
BUT YOU'VE GOT

15:35.750 --> 15:36.750
{\an1}TO COME BACK, MEL.

15:36.810 --> 15:37.780
{\an1}WE'RE A TEAM.

15:37.850 --> 15:39.020
{\an1}NO, KRUSTY.

15:39.080 --> 15:40.950
{\an1}YOU ALWAYS TREATED ME
RATHER SHABBILY.

15:41.020 --> 15:43.920
{\an1}ON OUR LAST SHOW, YOU POURED
LIQUID NITROGEN DOWN MY PANTS

15:43.990 --> 15:45.690
{\an1}AND CRACKED MY BUTTOCKS
\h\h\h\hWITH A HAMMER.

15:45.760 --> 15:46.820
{\an1}OH, COME ON.

15:46.890 --> 15:48.090
{\an1}DO YOU WANT
TO WASTE YOUR LIFE

15:48.160 --> 15:50.630
{\an1}HANGING OUT WITH A BUNCH
\h\h\hOF DORKY TEENAGERS?

15:50.700 --> 15:51.870
{\an1}HERE'S YOUR TACO, MISTER.

15:51.930 --> 15:52.860
{\an1}WHOOPS.

15:52.930 --> 15:53.860
{\an1}IT FELL IN THE FRYER.

15:53.930 --> 15:54.870
{\an1}I'LL GET IT OUT.

15:54.930 --> 15:56.430
{\an1}OW! OW!

15:56.500 --> 15:58.940
{\an1}<i>OW! <i>OW!</i></i>

15:59.000 --> 16:00.900
{\an1}SORRY, KRUSTY,
I LIKE IT HERE.

16:00.970 --> 16:02.870
{\an1}MR. JOHANSSEN TREATS ME
\h\h\h\h\hWITH DIGNITY.

16:02.940 --> 16:04.940
{\an1}\hIS THIS CLOWN
BOTHERING YOU, MEL?

16:05.010 --> 16:06.140
{\an1}THAT'S ALL RIGHT,
\hMR. JOHANSSEN.

16:06.210 --> 16:07.780
{\an1}I'LL HANDLE IT.

16:07.850 --> 16:08.980
{\an1}HERE'S YOUR TACO, SIR.

16:09.050 --> 16:10.210
{\an1}I DON'T WANT IT.

16:10.280 --> 16:11.580
{\an1}BUT THIS COMES OUT
\h\h\hOF MY SALARY.

16:11.650 --> 16:13.920
{\an1}IF I HAD A GIRLFRIEND,
\h\h\h\hSHE'D KILL ME.

16:13.990 --> 16:16.500
{\an1}Man: <i>OKAY, KRUSTY,
LET'S REHEARSE
THE BALLOON BIT.</i>

16:17.860 --> 16:18.620
{\an1}LOOK, KIDS!

16:20.090 --> 16:21.830
{\an1}A HORSEY!

16:21.890 --> 16:24.260
{\an1}AND WHAT ARE YOU MAKING,
\h\hSIDESHOW LUKE PERRY?

16:26.530 --> 16:28.100
{\an1}A 19th CENTURY CAROUSEL.

16:31.340 --> 16:32.370
{\an1}( <i>yelling )</i>

16:32.440 --> 16:33.670
{\an1}UPSTAGE ME, WILL YOU!

16:33.740 --> 16:35.110
{\an1}GET THE HELL OUT!

16:35.170 --> 16:37.680
{\an1}LOOK, THERE MUST BE
SOMETHING I CAN DO
ON THE SHOW.

16:37.740 --> 16:39.910
{\an1}PLEASE, FOR MOM'S SAKE.

16:39.980 --> 16:43.210
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hWELL, MAYBE
WE CAN FIND SOMETHING.

16:45.650 --> 16:46.520
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

16:49.990 --> 16:51.420
{\an1}( <i>evil laughing )</i>

16:58.460 --> 16:59.700
{\an1}I DON'T LIKE IT.

16:59.760 --> 17:01.600
{\an1}HE'S GOT JOHNNY CARSON,
\h\h\h\h\hBETTE MIDLER

17:01.670 --> 17:02.870
{\an1}<i>AND HUGH HEFNER.</i>

17:02.930 --> 17:03.830
{\an1}WHAT DO WE GOT?

17:03.900 --> 17:05.670
{\an1}RAY JAY JOHNSON.

17:05.740 --> 17:09.339
{\an1}AY-YI-YI-YI-YI-YI-YI-YI.

17:10.810 --> 17:13.079
{\an1}NOW BOYS, THE NETWORK
\h\h\h\hHAS A PROBLEM

17:13.140 --> 17:14.410
{\an1}WITH SOME OF YOUR LYRICS.

17:14.480 --> 17:16.010
{\an1}WOULD YOU MIND CHANGING THEM
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hFOR THE SHOW?

17:16.079 --> 17:17.510
{\an1}FORGET YOU, CLOWN.

17:17.579 --> 17:19.020
{\an1}\h\hHEY, OUR LYRICS ARE
LIKE OUR CHILDREN, MAN.

17:19.079 --> 17:20.520
{\an1}NO WAY.

17:20.589 --> 17:22.700
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hWELL, OKAY.
BUT HERE WHERE YOU SAY,

17:22.750 --> 17:24.960
{\an1}"WHAT I GOT YOU GOT TO GET
\h\h\h\hAND PUT IT IN YOU."

17:25.020 --> 17:28.190
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hHOW ABOUT JUST,
"WHAT I'D LIKE IS I'D LIKE
\h\h\hTO HUG AND KISS YOU."

17:28.260 --> 17:29.960
{\an1}WOW.

17:30.030 --> 17:31.400
{\an1}THAT'S MUCH BETTER.

17:31.460 --> 17:32.960
{\an1}EVERYONE CAN ENJOY <i>THAT.</i>

17:33.030 --> 17:34.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHost:
<i>LIVE FROM SPRINGFIELD</i>

17:34.800 --> 17:36.600
{\an1}<i>THE ENTERTAINMENT CAPITAL
\h\h\h\h\h\hOF THIS STATE,</i>

17:36.670 --> 17:38.700
{\an1}<i>THE KRUSTY KOMEBACK SPECIAL.</i>

17:42.310 --> 17:45.240
{\an1}♪ SEND IN... ♪

17:45.310 --> 17:49.010
{\an1}♪ THE CLOWNS ♪

17:49.080 --> 17:54.450
{\an1}♪ THOSE DAFFY, LAUGHY CLOWNS ♪

17:54.520 --> 17:58.490
{\an1}♪ SEND IN THOSE SOULFUL
\h\h\h\h\hAND DOLEFUL ♪

17:58.560 --> 18:04.090
{\an1}♪ SCHMALTZ-BY-THE-BOWLFUL
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hCLOWNS ♪

18:06.360 --> 18:10.430
{\an1}♪ SEND IN THE CLOWNS... ♪

18:10.500 --> 18:11.640
{\an1}( <i>sobbing )</i>

18:13.200 --> 18:19.010
{\an1}♪ THEY'RE ALREADY HERE. ♪

18:23.310 --> 18:26.120
{\an1}( <i>audience applauding )</i>

18:28.790 --> 18:30.090
{\an1}I LOVE YOU, KRUSTY.

18:30.150 --> 18:31.620
{\an1}QUIET.

18:33.390 --> 18:35.360
{\an1}( <i>drum roll )</i>

18:36.860 --> 18:39.500
{\an1}ARE YOU COMFORTABLE IN THERE,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hLUKE PERRY?

18:39.560 --> 18:40.830
{\an1}FIRE AWAY, KRUSTY.

18:40.900 --> 18:41.770
{\an1}( <i>loud blast )</i>

18:41.830 --> 18:43.770
{\an1}( <i>Luke yelling )</i>

18:43.830 --> 18:45.740
{\an1}( <i>loud crashing )</i>

18:48.970 --> 18:50.040
{\an1}OH, MY FACE!

18:50.110 --> 18:51.390
{\an1}MY VALUABLE FACE!

18:52.630 --> 18:53.260
{\an1}HMPH.

18:55.600 --> 18:56.500
{\an1}( <i>sighs )</i>

18:59.170 --> 19:00.330
{\an1}( <i>explosion )</i>

19:00.400 --> 19:01.570
{\an1}( <i>Luke yelling )</i>

19:02.900 --> 19:03.800
{\an1}( <i>chuckling nervously )</i>

19:03.870 --> 19:04.940
{\an1}AY...

19:07.140 --> 19:09.510
{\an1}♪ GIVE IT AWAY, GIVE IT AWAY
\h\h\h\h\hGIVE IT AWAY NOW ♪

19:09.580 --> 19:12.010
{\an1}♪ GIVE IT AWAY, GIVE IT AWAY
\h\h\h\h\hGIVE IT AWAY NOW ♪

19:12.080 --> 19:14.750
{\an1}\h♪ I CAN'T TELL IF I'M
A KINGPIN OR A PAUPER ♪

19:14.820 --> 19:16.380
{\an1}\h\hDANCING AROUND
IN THEIR UNDERWEAR.

19:16.450 --> 19:18.650
{\an1}THAT IS SO DEGRADING.

19:18.720 --> 19:20.590
{\an1}\h30 SECONDS TILL YOUR
LITTLE STINKER SKETCH.

19:20.650 --> 19:22.260
{\an1}GIVE ME A BIGGER LOLLY.

19:22.320 --> 19:24.830
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hNOW, JOHNNY,
WHAT DO YOU GOT FOR US?

19:24.890 --> 19:26.830
{\an1}SOME JOKES? A LITTLE MAGIC?

19:26.890 --> 19:29.160
{\an1}ACTUALLY, I THOUGHT
I'D LIFT THIS 1987

19:29.230 --> 19:30.760
{\an1}BUICK SKYLARK
OVER MY HEAD.

19:33.130 --> 19:34.230
{\an1}HI-YO!

19:34.300 --> 19:35.700
{\an1}JOHNNY, THAT'S AMAZING.

19:35.770 --> 19:37.340
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hOH, YEAH?
GET A LOAD OF THIS.

19:37.410 --> 19:40.180
{\an1}( <i>singing aria from Carmen <i>)</i></i>

19:50.620 --> 19:52.950
{\an1}( <i>playing music from "Amahl
\h\hAnd The Night Visitors" )</i>

19:55.520 --> 19:58.290
{\an1}I'VE GOT TO FIRE THAT AGENT.

19:58.360 --> 20:01.300
{\an1}( <i>piano striking up )</i>

20:01.360 --> 20:06.070
{\an1}\h\h♪ DID YOU EVER KNOW
THAT YOU'RE MY HERO? ♪

20:08.770 --> 20:13.440
{\an1}\h♪ YOU'RE EVERYTHING
I WOULD LIKE TO BE ♪

20:16.140 --> 20:20.810
{\an1}♪ YOU CAN FLY HIGHER
\h\h\hTHAN AN EAGLE ♪

20:23.450 --> 20:24.720
{\an1}♪ 'CAUSE YOU ARE THE WIND ♪

20:24.790 --> 20:25.790
{\an1}♪ 'CAUSE I AM THE WIND

20:25.850 --> 20:27.050
{\an1}♪ BENEATH MY WINGS. ♪

20:27.120 --> 20:29.720
{\an1}♪ BENEATH YOUR WINGS. ♪

20:29.790 --> 20:31.560
{\an1}( <i>sobbing )</i>

20:38.600 --> 20:40.670
{\an1}THIS WAS A GREAT SHOW,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hKRUSTY.

20:40.730 --> 20:42.270
{\an1}\h\h\hYOU DESERVE
AN EMMY FOR THIS.

20:42.340 --> 20:43.270
{\an1}FORGET IT.

20:43.340 --> 20:44.440
{\an1}THE ACADEMY HATES ME.

20:44.510 --> 20:45.980
{\an1}I DON'T KNOW WHY.

20:46.040 --> 20:48.010
{\an1}BUNCH OF OLD KNOW-NOTHING
DINOSAURS

20:48.080 --> 20:50.040
{\an1}WOULDN'T KNOW ENTERTAINMENT
\hIF IT BIT THEM IN THE...

20:50.110 --> 20:52.510
{\an1}HEY, HEY!

20:52.580 --> 20:55.180
{\an1}( <i>people chattering )</i>

20:55.250 --> 20:57.480
{\an1}( <i>bell clanging )</i>

20:57.550 --> 20:58.890
{\an1}( <i>buzzing )</i>

21:00.720 --> 21:02.820
{\an1}NOW, KRUSTY,
I JUST HOPE YOU REMEMBER

21:02.890 --> 21:04.460
{\an1}TO SAVE YOUR MONEY
\h\h\h\hTHIS TIME.

21:04.530 --> 21:06.840
{\an1}\h\h\hHERE'S THAT RUBY-STUDDED
CLOWN NOSE YOU ORDERED, KRUSTY.

21:08.200 --> 21:10.100
{\an1}( <i>crying )</i>

21:10.160 --> 21:10.930
{\an1}AY...

21:11.000 --> 21:13.070
{\an1}WHAT'S UP, MOE?

21:13.130 --> 21:15.800
{\an1}HEY. YOU CAN'T COME IN HERE
\h\h\h\hDRESSED LIKE THAT.

21:15.870 --> 21:17.200
{\an1}GET WITH THE TIMES, MOE.

21:17.270 --> 21:18.370
{\an1}YEAH. I SAY

21:18.440 --> 21:20.540
{\an1}IF IT FEELS GOOD, DO IT.

21:20.610 --> 21:21.240
{\an1}ALL RIGHT.

21:22.780 --> 21:24.780
{\an1}( <i>laughing )</i>

21:24.850 --> 21:26.010
{\an1}DON'T SNAP MY UNDIES.

21:27.450 --> 21:29.120
{\an1}I'M A STAR AGAIN.

21:29.180 --> 21:31.080
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hI DON'T KNOW
HOW TO THANK YOU, KIDS.

21:31.150 --> 21:32.690
{\an1}THAT'S ALL RIGHT, KRUSTY.

21:32.750 --> 21:34.890
{\an1}WE'RE GETTING 50 PERCENT
\h\hOF THE T-SHIRT SALES.

21:34.960 --> 21:35.920
{\an1}WHAT?!

21:35.990 --> 21:37.660
{\an1}THAT'S THE SWEETEST PLUM!

21:37.730 --> 21:39.400
{\an1}YOU LITTLE...

21:39.460 --> 21:41.430
{\an1}AHH... WHAT THE HELL.

21:41.500 --> 21:42.830
{\an1}YOU DESERVE IT.

21:42.900 --> 21:44.230
{\an1}THANKS, KIDS.

21:44.300 --> 21:45.800
{\an1}TO KRUSTY--

21:45.870 --> 21:48.140
{\an1}THE GREATEST ENTERTAINER
\h\h\h\h\h\hIN THE WORLD.

21:49.300 --> 21:50.500
